text: Icelus may refer to: * Icelus or Icelos, another name for Phobetor, in Ovid's Metamorphoses * Icelus (genus), a genus of fishes * Icelus, a freedman who served the Roman Emperor Galba before his downfall * A character in Saint Seiya: The Lost Canvas ==See also== * Erynnis icelus, (dreamy duskywing), a butterfly
title: Icelus
